As I went along Houndsditch one morning about eight o'clock there was a great noise . 
But the outcry was loud enough to prompt my curiosity , and I called to one that looked out of a window , and asked what was the matter . 
A watchman , it seems , had been employed to keep his post at the door of a house which was infected , or said to be infected , and was shut up . 
This , it seems , was about one o'clock . 
Soon after , as the fellow said , he stopped the dead cart , and then knocked again , but nobody answered . 
The watchman knew not what to make of all this , so he let them alone till the morning man or day watchman , as they called him , came to relieve him . 
