It is true people used all possible precaution . 
When any one bought a joint of meat in the market they would not take it off the butcher's hand , but took it off the hooks themselves . 
On the other hand , the butcher would not touch the money , but have it put into a pot full of vinegar , which he kept for that purpose . 
The buyer carried always small money to make up any odd sum , that they might take no change . 
Innumerable dismal stories we heard every day on this very account . 
