No , brother , you mistake the case , and mistake me too . 
But they do not deny you liberty to go back again from whence you came , and therefore they do not starve you . 
But the next town behind me will , by the same rule , deny me leave to go back , and so they do starve me between them . 
Besides , there is no law to prohibit my travelling wherever I will on the road . 
Why , brother , our condition at this rate is worse than anybody else's , for we can neither go away nor stay here . 
There is no lying in the street at such a time as this we had as good go into the dead cart at once . 
Therefore I say , if we stay here we are sure to die , and if we go away we can but die I am resolved to be gone . 
