The first night they encamped all in the forest , and not far off of one another , but not setting up the tent , lest that should discover them . 
The provisions they had at Walthamstow served them very plentifully this night and as for the next , they left it to Providence . 
They had fared so well with the old soldier's conduct that they now willingly made him their leader , and the first of his conduct appeared to be very good . 
They all referred themselves to his direction , so they left their three houses standing , and the next day went away towards Epping . 
