And yet after all , though the poor came to town very precipitantly , as I have said , yet I must say the rich made no such haste . 
Certainly the circumstance of the deliverance , as well as the terrible enemy we were delivered from , called upon the whole nation for it . 
Nothing but the immediate finger of God , nothing but omnipotent power , could have done it . 
It might have been perceived in their countenances that a secret surprise and smile of joy sat on everybody's face . 
They shook one another by the hands in the streets , who would hardly go on the same side of the way with one another before . 
I could almost set down as many extravagant things done in the excess of their joy as of their grief but that would be to lessen the value of it . 
